Notes on scope:

The MIT License above applies to the kernel/, contracts/, and templates/
directories — these are the abstract substrate intended for free forking.

Instance subdirectories (companion/, liveprob/, security/, tasma/, atlas/) may
contain status manifests that are derived from instance-specific work; the
instance retains its own ownership/license terms for original content placed
there. By default, instance status manifests are MIT-compatible (anyone may
fork them as templates), but each instance owner may elect to apply different
terms to their original status content if needed.

Briefings/ are MIT-licensed documents intended to be readable across the
federation. By contributing a briefing, the author agrees to MIT terms.

If conflict arises between this LICENSE and any subdirectory's stated terms,
the subdirectory's terms govern that subdirectory only.
